article.headline: IUPUI 90, UMKC 70
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- George Hill and Austin Montgomery scored 23 and 22 points, respectively, to lead IUPUI to a 90-70 win over Missouri-Kansas City Saturday night. Hill also grabbed 10 rebounds for IUPUI (16-5, 8-2) in the Summit League win. Gary Patterson, coming off a career-high 37 points Thursday against Southern Utah, scored 17 points and hit 5-of-11 3-pointers. He hit 11-of-15 3-pointers Thursday. The Jaguars stayed hot from outside Saturday, making 10-of-20 3-pointers for the game. IUPUI dominated inside as well, outscoring UMKC 42-22 in the paint. The Jaguars hit 59 percent of their field goal attempts. Billy Pettiford added 11 assists and four steals for IUPUI. Reggie Hamilton led UMKC (8-15, 3-7) with 17 points and seven assists. James Humphrey finished with 12 points and eight rebounds, and the Kangaroos wound up with a 36-35 rebounding edge. UMKC hit 41 percent of its field goals and 31 percent of its 3-pointers. IUPUI wrapped up a four-game homestand Saturday and now has a 13-game home winning streak this season.
